This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as named entity segmentation and sentiment classification, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of word embeddings, which is a popular topic in machine learning and deep learning, falling under categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of feature engineering, which is a common theme in information retrieval (cs.IR).
